The paper deals with the practical implementation of machine learning algorithms, specifically the impact of quantization on learning. This topic is most closely related to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG), which is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the convergence of algorithms, which is related to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses datasets that are commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper proposes a formalization for reasoning about quantization, which is related to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
